    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-25T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/957: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-25T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 25, 1934—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 26—2 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Mayor Vienna informs me Chancellor Dollfuss has died of bleeding result two
                    shots in the neck and that Schuschnigg is acting at the request of the President
                    until return of Vice Chancellor Starhemberg tomorrow morning from Italy where he
                    has been on holiday.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office has been cleared and the prisoners estimated at well over 100 have
                    been taken to the police prison.</p>
                <p>President Miklas returns to Vienna by special train arriving tomorrow
                    morning.</p>
                <p>Foregoing now officially confirmed in Government statement. All reports and
                    personal observation staff confirm city quiet. Official and other sources
                    confirm quiet throughout country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
